UN Secretary-General Antonio Guterres called to establish accountability after military personnel of the UN Organization Stabilization Mission in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (MONUSCO) opened fire on Sunday while returning from leave in their home country. Two people were reportedly killed and several others injured by the UN peacekeepers. "The Secretary-General is both saddened and dismayed by the loss of life and serious injuries sustained during this incident," according to statement from the UN spokesperson. "The Secretary-General stresses in the strongest terms the need to establish accountability for these events," it added.